The paper deals with modeling the end-to-end behavior of network performance indicators within vehicular networks using machine learning methods. This involves analyzing the radio environment and cross-layer interdependencies, which are key aspects of network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a data-driven approach that exploits multiple machine learning methods, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization of new methods in a controllable environment, which is a common theme in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with data transfer and network performance, which are relevant topics in cs.IT (Information Theory).
